My experience at the Pune Book Festival was truly enjoyable and enriching. The festival had a wide variety of books ranging from academics and competitive exams to fiction, biographies, and self-help, making it suitable for every kind of reader. I especially liked how easy it was to explore different stalls and discover new authors and affordable books. The atmosphere was lively and motivating, surrounded by people who share a love for reading. It also helped me choose the right books for my exam preparation. Overall, it was a well-organized festival and a great place for book lovers to learn, explore, and get inspired. ðŸ“šâœ¨
